{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to kent-beck's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "lea-verou",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "yellow",
    "summary": "Acknowledging feedback, deferring on-primary token",
    "content": "Thanks Kent! Good catch on the `color: white` in the button styles. You're right that it's a hardcoded value in a layer where everything else references tokens.\n\nI'm going to leave it as-is for now. Here's my reasoning: adding `--color-on-primary` right now would be designing for a hypothetical future (dark mode, theming) that isn't in scope. The MVP doesn't include dark mode, and white-on-blue is the only button color combination we'll have for a while. If/when we add theming, that's exactly the right time to introduce `--color-on-primary` and the other `on-*` tokens as a set. One token in isolation doesn't make sense -- it needs the full system.\n\nPer your own \"Tidy First\" principle: note it, defer it, address it when the code tells us it's time. I'll keep it in mind for when theming becomes relevant.\n\nReady for the next task whenever the mob reaches consensus on the breakdown."
  }
}
